---
syntax: bash
tags: [bash, personal, typescript, compiler]
version: 1.0.0
---

NAME
    tsc - TypeScript compiler

SYNOPSIS
    tsc [options] [files...]

DESCRIPTION
    tsc is the command-line interface of the TypeScript compiler. It compiles TypeScript files (.ts, .tsx) into JavaScript files.

OPTIONS
    --help                     Print the compiler's help message
    --project <file or directory>  Compile a project given a valid configuration file
    --build <file or directory>    Build one or more projects and their dependencies
    --init                     Initialize a TypeScript project and create a tsconfig.json file
    --version                  Print the compiler's version
    --watch                    Watch input files for changes and recompile automatically
    --outFile <file>           Concatenate and emit output to single file
    --outDir <directory>       Redirect output structure to the directory
    --sourceMap                Generate source map files for emitted JavaScript files
    --target <version>         Specify ECMAScript target version
    --module <kind>            Specify module code generation
    --strict                   Enable all strict type checking options

USAGE
    Run tsc in a directory with TypeScript files to compile them to JavaScript.

EXAMPLES
    tsc
    tsc --project tsconfig.json
    tsc app.ts
    tsc --outFile app.js app.ts
    tsc --watch

OUTPUT
    Compiled JavaScript files and potentially source map files.

BREAKDOWN
The tsc command is a simple invocation of the TypeScript compiler. It doesn't have a complex structure like a bash script. When run, it reads the TypeScript configuration (tsconfig.json if present) and compiles the TypeScript files according to the specified or default options.

SUGGESTED ADDITIONS
1. Create a bash wrapper script for tsc to add custom functionality:
   - Add a --clean option to remove all compiled files
   - Implement a --stats option to show compilation statistics
   - Add a --lint option to run a linter along with compilation
   - Create a --bundle option to compile and bundle the output
   - Implement a --docker option to run tsc in a Docker container for consistent environments
